    • Class curam.core.struct.SearchServiceDtls extends Struct<SearchServiceDtls> implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -1812537655L

      • Serialized Fields

        • searchServiceId

          java.lang.String searchServiceId
          A string used to uniquely identify a Search Service.

        • extKeyName

          java.lang.String extKeyName
          The name of a Search Service Field that will uniquely identify each record in an Index created from this Search Service definition. It is essential that values in the Index corresponding to this Search Service Field be unique, as when searchable data is updated in the Curam database, the value of this field will be used to identify the appropriate Document to be updated in the Index.

        • analyzer

          java.lang.String analyzer
          The Search Service analyzer to be used when converting from Curam database text terms to Index terms. The contents of this column should denote one of the predefined analyzer names provided by the Generic Search Server (see the list below) or a fully qualified Java classname of a class that implements the abstract class org.apache.lucene.analysis.Analyzer. This may be either a standard Lucene analyzer or a third-party or custom implementation. Note that the class must be available on the Generic Search Server classpath if it is not a standard Lucene analyzer. The Generic Search Server provides the following predefined analyzers. STANDARD Splits text at punctuation characters, removing punctuation. However, a dot that's not followed by whitespace is considered part of a token. Splits words at hyphens, unless there's a number in the token, in which case the whole token is interpreted as a product number and is not split. Recognizes email addresses and internet hostnames as one token. Normalizes token text to lower case and removes common English stop words. SIMPLE Splits text at non-letter characters and normalizes token text to lower case. STOP Curam Generic Search Server 14 Splits text at non-letter characters, normalizes token text to lower case and removes common English stop words. WHITESPACE Splits text at whitespace. Adjacent sequences of non-Whitespace characters form tokens. KEYWORD \"Tokenizes\" the entire stream as a single token. This is useful for data like zip codes, ids, and some product names.

        • frcedReidxTimeStmp

          DateTime frcedReidxTimeStmp
          Used by the Extractor to force the Generic Search Server to rebuild its Indices after an extract has been run. When creating Search Service records, this should be initially set to null.

        • mapperName

          java.lang.String mapperName
          The name of the mapper implementation (see GSS Developer's Guide, Implement Mapper Operations). A Mapper implementation is a class that converts a set of Curam entity data to a format suitable for indexing. The value of this column should be the fully qualified classname of the Mapper class, and as with the Analyzer implementation, this should be on the Generic Search Server runtime classpath (If the Mapper is developed as part of the Curam application it will be on the classpath by default).

          MAPPER_NAME_STRING -> String

        • dbLastWritten

          DateTime dbLastWritten
          The time the persisted index was last written to the database. Used to allow the persisted index to be supplemented with more recent data when starting up.

        • prstBlobSize

          java.lang.String prstBlobSize
          The blob size to be used when persisting this search service.

    • Class curam.core.struct.SearchServiceFieldDtls extends Struct<SearchServiceFieldDtls> implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      1873411174L

      • Serialized Fields

        • srchServiceFldId

          java.lang.String srchServiceFldId
          The Unique Identifier of the Search Service Field.

        • searchServiceId

          java.lang.String searchServiceId
          SearchServiceId of the parent Search Service record.

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          The name associated with the Search Service Field. This is the name that is used to reference the Field when performing searches or retrieving results. It does not need to correspond exactly to Field names in Curam entities and structs, although it simplifies development if it does so.

        • indexed

          boolean indexed
          Indicates whether this Field is searchable. Sometimes it may be desirable to store a value for a record in the Search Service but not to search on it (an example would be the unique ID of a record, or perhaps it's sensitivity level). Not indexing values that don't need to be indexed will minimize Index size and help performance, so it is good practice to index only the fields your searches will use.

        • type

          java.lang.String type
          The Curam datatype of this field. The set of acceptable values is described in the GSS Developer's Guide. The process of exporting and synchronizing data to the Search Service involves some conversion of operational data to strings and vice-versa, so it is important that an accurate data type be defined for each Field. See the following table for reference on this. If incorrect values are presented to the Generic Search Server, it will throw an exception.

        • stored

          boolean stored
          Indicates whether this field may be returned in a search result or not, i.e. whether the value itself is stored in the Index. Note that stored fields will still only be returned if the Query object passed to the Generic Search Server indicates that they should be returned. Every field should be either indexed or stored or both - if a field is neither then it is of no relevance to the Search Service. Again, not storing values that your searches will not use will minimize index size and help performance, so only store the fields your searches will use.

        • entityName

          java.lang.String entityName
          The name of the Curam entity associated with this Field, or to be more specific, the name of the Curam Entity containing an attribute corresponding to this Field which will be used to populate the Index based on the parent Search Service definition. This information is needed for synchronization of application data with the Generic Search Server - all entities that are listed as being related to Search Service Fields will be registered with the Search- Controller (see Section 3.4, Search Controller) and monitored for inserts, updates, and deletions. It is vitally important that the entityName attribute be populated with the appropriate values; omitted or invalid entityName attributes may result in invalid Index updates over time.

          SEARCH_SERVICE_STRING -> String

        • untokenized

          boolean untokenized
          This property indicates whether a field is to be tokenized and passed through the analyzer or not. It is a boolean value. If set to true, no tokenizing will be done and analysis will not be performed on this field before indexing or while searching.

        • analyzerName

          java.lang.String analyzerName
          This property specifies the analyzer to be used when tokenizing this field. The contents of this field may be set to STANDARD,SIMPLE,STOP, WHITESPACE,KEYBOARD. (see analyzer in Section 5.2, SearchService Table) If this field is not set then the default analyzer used will be that taken from the analyzer field of the associated SearchService.
